===Etymology===
From {{proto|Indo-European|bʰleh₃-|flower, blossom|lang=la}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|bʰel-|lang=la|to bloom|title=}}.  Cognates include Ancient Greek {{term|φύλλον|tr=phullon|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}, Gothic {{term|sc=Goth|𐌱𐌻𐍉𐌼𐌰|tr=blōma|lang=got}} and Old English {{term|blostm|blōstm|lang=ang}}, {{term|blæd||leaf|lang=ang}} (English {{term|blossom|lang=en}}, {{term|blade|lang=en}}).

